Probably a question to ask on the pytorch-YOLOv4 repo. However, there seems to be an example of pre-processing the input, running the model, and processing the output in the demo_darknet2onnx.py scrip. Does that not work for you?

https://github.com/Tianxiaomo/pytorch-YOLOv4/blob/4ccef0ec8fe984e059378813e33b3740929e0c19/demo_darknet2onnx.py#L32

This line is executing the model with onnxruntime: https://github.com/Tianxiaomo/pytorch-YOLOv4/blob/4ccef0ec8fe984e059378813e33b3740929e0c19/demo_darknet2onnx.py#L47

we are trying out the onnx model on web so python preprocessing won't help and we are able to run the model but we are getting a 1d array for boxes whereas we should get an array of 4 like n X 4 type array. I guess it might be the preprocessing code that is messing up the output. you can see the preprocess function below here

https://github.com/sambitraze/tfjsdemo/tree/main/onnxweb2

You can view the onnx model in [Netron](https://netron.app/) to see the expected input and outputs (names and shapes). The output shapes can only be affected by the input shapes, and I don't believe it's possible for the number of dimensions in each output to change. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/979079/138176100-4929d6ee-434d-450c-9581-8a25edcd64cf.png)

If that outputs and its shape isn't what you'd expect it would be something to do with the model export from pytorch.

The return type of run() is not a just array, but Tensors associated with output names. You can check API in [here](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/api/js/interfaces/InferenceSession.html#run).

And, here is the result of your example and looks like working as expected.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35605090/138180131-2eb30d93-5376-43fc-8dae-521d2cb0f2c4.png)
We have a demo for a yolo model [here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-web-demo/blob/main/src/components/models/Yolo.vue).

Check the inputs/outputs of your model and the preprocessing required vs the existing demo we have and adjust accordingly.

If you want someone to create a demo for you I'd suggest searching for a freelance software engineer to do the work.

Where can I find anchor boxes for tiny yolo v4. I have the anchor boxes in INT format but according to @hanbitmyths' example, I need it to be a floating array (the same can be found here in line 9 https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-web-demo/blob/main/src/utils/yolo.ts this is the example of yolo v3 )
